</div>
</div>
<div class="container white mostly fadein">

  <h2>Problem: Wine producers don’t give consumers the information they need to make informed purchase decisions.</h2>
  <h2>Solution: Walk consumers through the history of a wine's vineyard in virtual reality to uncover the story of the region and the craft of winemaking.</h2>
</div>
<div class="container full white fadein">
  <p>During my time at Fresh Tilled Soil, I worked independently on a product in the food and drink industry. After rounds of research and prototyping, I ended up building a virtual reality experience.</p>
  <figure>
    <img class="full" src="../img/studies/winevr/lookaround.gif" alt=""/>
    <figcaption>An early title shot from the Columbia River Valley prototype, later scrapped. The sun sets as the user progresses through the valley.</figcaption>
  </figure>
  <p>Prior to my research, I knew nothing about wine, so diving into the wine industry was a fascinating learning experience. Thanks to the generosity of many passionate wine industry people up and down the supply chain, I gained a glimpse of a world of craft, commerce, and  agriculture.</p>
</div>
<figure>
  <img src="../img/studies/wineux/industry.gif" class="full" alt="The wine industry supply chain by need, tools, and obstacles" />
